sentence: Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) will begin trading ex-dividend on November 28, 2018.
A cash dividend payment of $1.03 per share is scheduled to be paid on December 13, 2018.
Shareholders who purchased HD prior to the ex-dividend date are eligible for the cash dividend payment.
This marks the 4th quarter that HD has paid the same dividend.
At the current stock price of $169.82, the dividend yield is 2.43%.
The previous trading day's last sale of HD was $169.82, representing a -21.17% decrease from the 52 week high of $215.43 and a 1.69% increase over the 52 week low of $167.
HD is a part of the Consumer Services sector, which includes companies such as Lowe's Companies, Inc. ( LOW ) and Sherwin-Williams Company ( SHW ).
HD's current earnings per share, an indicator of a company's profitability, is $9.16.
Zacks Investment Research reports HD's forecasted earnings growth in 2019 as 31.2%, compared to an industry average of 23.7%.
For more information on the declaration, record and payment dates, visit the HD Dividend History page.
